Echinochloa frumentacea

   [5597.jpg]
    Authority   Link
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms   Echinochloa colona var. frumentacea (Link) Ridl.
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5597

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A grass with tall, erect culms reaching a height of
   90-200 cm. USES It can be grown as a substitute for rice. It can be
   mixed with rice and fermented to make beer. It can also be grown as a
   fodder crop.
   GROWING PERIOD Summer-growing annual grass. The quickest growing of all
   millets, will produce a crop in about 40-45 days and matures in 120
   days. In United States it has produced as many as 8 crops a year.
   COMMON NAMES Japanese millet, Japanese barnyard millet, Billion dollar
   grass, White panicum, Siberian millet. FURTHER INF Scientific synonym:
   E. colonum var frumentacea, E. crusgalli var frumentacea, Panicum
   frumentacea. Japanese millet is cultivated in South-East Asia. It can
   be found at elevations between sea level and 1500 m. It is common in
   cultivations and naturalized in wet grassland. Yields of up to 35 t/ha
   of green material can be obtained.

